Hello! Here's a pack of eight maps in total I've ported over the span of some time. Some ports are incomplete, meaning anything between 90-95% complete, and this WILL be updated overtime.
This pack contains (1-2) kz/bhop maps, and the rest are native bunnyhop maps. These maps were ported directly from Counter-Strike 1.6, and have not been modified, aside from some aspects of gameplay rendered useless, or not possible to complete.

Hope you enjoy.

MAPS-

bhop_cd - Map by CD, https://cosy-climbing.net/maps.php/4189/cd_bhop/

bhop_essy_jumps - Map by Whitey, https://cosy-climbing.net/user.php?id.95

bhop_viva_peron - Map by Paty, https://cosy-climbing.net/user.php?id.1459

bhop_dustbhop_notkz - Map by ???, https://cosy-climbing.net/maps.php/2076/notkz_dust...

bhop_leetbhop - Map by NAPZ, https://cosy-climbing.net/user.php?id.1396

bhop_average_bhop_gbc - Map by Gorbachev, https://cosy-climbing.net/user.php?id.4076

bhop_hop - Map by z1820, https://cosy-climbing.net/user.php?id.318

kz_bhop_brickbhop - Map by mH, https://cosy-climbing.net/user.php?id.172

KNOWN ISSUES/BUGS:

bhop_cd

-FPS drops/issues around later stages of map, unknown cause

-Buggy decompiling issues with MBSPC not translating skybox nodraw correctly

bhop_essy_jumps

-Random light at end, due to the way the original KZ timer for 1.6 worked the prefab for the end timer always contained a light, CBA to remove as it adds some semblence of ambience.

bhop_viva_peron

-Buggy/Shitty texture work, decided not to re-do it, maybe will update archive if I get around to it no guarantees.

-No music, I thought it was obnoxious and unnecessary.

bhop_leetbhop

-Some minor leaks on the brushwork, not entirely fixable due to the way the brushes decompile with MBSPC if I try it breaks the entire map completely, but the entire map should work absolutely fine. 100% playable with no bugs.

bhop_hop

-Possibly some leaks outside of the map, and buggy texture work at the end. No idea what causes either as the pointfile indicates something of nil value. Will possibly look into it.

NOTE:

I didn't bother updating the textures with new ones, as this is a preservation account, nor did I make these maps myself so I don't consider myself at any right to modify other mappers work.

TEXTURES WILL BE BLURRY AND BAD LOOKING IF YOU USE A LOW TEXTURE SETTING. USE HIGH TEXTURE SETTINGS FOR BEST APPEARANCE!

This was my first map that I converted to source and the first one I have finished. Shotty_courtyard Players spawn with a shot gun and knife. Under the middle are 2 weapon dispensers that have auto shotguns with 21 extra rounds. It can only be activated once per round. The opposite side of spawn has a ladder to reach the upper level. On the upper level are 2 more weapon dispensers they both have scouts. It can only be activated once per round and only have the default 10 rounds each. When I made this map. I only made it to do a time lapse of making a quick playable map. All I did was start and kept going to i was finished with the lower level. Then it took 5 month to finally finish it for source. A map based on the game tetris. In this map the T's start at the top of the map and have to go down to the bombsites and plant. The CTs have to defend them. all colored and white blocks are destructable (some are stronger than others).

Everyone starts with an m3 however the Ts have some grenades and autoshotguns which they can also take from the ground.

The marked blocks can be made to move by using E (some of them are only once)

This map has 2 spawn places in seperate areas (both reachable for the other team - they are like bombsite B - screen 4). The center has 9 platform where you can easily jump to the next one by using the arrows. All platforms are marked with a color or logo. The center one is also a bombsite and has autoshotguns, it also has a wall to the CT side to prevent the bomber getting killed to easy (now they have to go to the other side or jump in). The floating arrows push you up and the logo above it is a teleport. All blocks with a logo on the side of a platform lead you to the spawnplace. Square and Cross are CT, Triangle and Circle are T.

Read the .txt for more information

Welcome to sg_de_colors !

This map is a low gravity fun map. Everyone gets a Knife, Shotgun and HE. there are 2 teleports marked with triangles with a autoshotgun in it. (your task is to find out how to get one). I have added 2 secret rooms (both are still in the same layout) with in each one a autoshotgun and smoke grenade. if you can also find the button in there you will hear that the secret is found. (its not hard to spot but the trick is to reach it)

The music is by elvis presley (it will be changed in a later version so it has more styles)

Final Update:
- The music is now changed with more styles
- The easter egg is now harder to abuse by camping
- Some light effects are added
- A new sort of jump arrow is added (gets unlocked by getting in the easter egg).
- The screens are still true with ingame (however the lights arent visible on it since the screens were from _b3)

The new music styles are 4 songs mixed to each other. the songs are by: Elvis, The Cure, Patrick Hernandez and Mc Hammer (however you most likely wont hear mc hammer much since the average round is pretty short)

Hint for the Easter egg: You can only get in by jumping on someone and then jumping in the easter egg area or by using the jump arrows (could need some practice)

Here we have my first map. Not too shabby if I do say so myself, but it could be Improved. While I'm not classifying it as and Alpha or Beta, I wouldn't call it final. Anyway, It's a large room with OVER THIRTY spawn points for each team. All the players start out with their USP or Glock, their trusty combat knife, and, of course, a Benelli M3 12 gauge shotgun! The game is played until every tango's met your lil' friend...

UPDATE:
I first posted this eight months ago, and never corrected my problem of mistakenly posting a VMT file instead of an actual map file. I have now added it and more! I have since added proper lighting and upped the number of shells that you start with. Enjoy version 1.1 of Conduit!
